summary:
The Security Council,
 Reaffirming resolutions on Cyprus, particularly 1250 (1999) aimed at a comprehensive settlement,
 Reiterating interest in a settlement considering relevant resolutions and treaties,
 Welcoming the Secretary-General's report (S/2003/398) on his Cyprus mission,

1. Commends the Secretary-General's effort since 1999 to achieve a Cyprus settlement;
2. Commends the Secretary-General for presenting a comprehensive settlement plan;
3. Regrets the Turkish Cypriot leader's negative approach prevented a simultaneous referenda;
4. Supports the Secretary-General's 26 February 2003 plan as a basis for negotiations;
5. Supports the Secretary-General's mission of Good Offices and asks him to continue;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
